FBIS4-44200 "drweu124_i_94004" FBIS-WEU-94-124 Daily Report 28 Jun 1994 FRANCE Leotard To Visit Troops Deployed on Rwandan Border Leotard To Visit Troops Deployed on Rwandan Border AU2806081494 Paris AFP in English GMT 28 Jun 94 AU2806081494 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Paris, June 28 (AFP) -- Defense Minister Francois Leotard is to leave here late Tuesday [28 June] to tour the Rwandan-Zairean border, where France is deploying 2,500 troops to protect civilians threatened by the Rwandan ethnic carnage, defense ministry officials said. The officials said Leotard would spend the whole of Wednesday in the area and would be accompanied by the junior minister for humanitarian action, Lucette Michaux-Chevry, or junior Health Minister Philippe Douste-Blazy.
